@startuml feature-invariants
title Feature Class — Invariants List\n(iDaVIE — DataFeatures namespace)

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor #555
  ArrowColor #333
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #888
}

class Feature {
  + Id : int
  + Name : string
  + Index : int
  + Flag : string
  + RawData : string[]
  + Temporary : bool
  + Metric : float
  + Comment : string
  + FeatureSetParent : FeatureSetRenderer
  - _selected : bool
  - _active : bool
  - _corners : Vector3[2]
  - _unityBounds : Bounds
  ..
  + CornerMin : Vector3 <<get>>
  + CornerMax : Vector3 <<get>>
  + Center : Vector3 <<get/set>>
  + Size : Vector3 <<get/set>>
  + Visible : bool <<get/set>>
  + Selected : bool <<get/set>>
  + UnityBounds : Bounds <<get>>
}

note top of Feature
  <b>SPATIAL / GEOMETRIC</b>

  INV-1: CornerMin.x <= CornerMax.x
         CornerMin.y <= CornerMax.y
         CornerMin.z <= CornerMax.z

  INV-2: Size.x >= 1, Size.y >= 1, Size.z >= 1
         (size is padded by one — bounding box
         includes both the min and max voxels)

  INV-3: Center == (CornerMin + CornerMax) / 2
         must hold at all times

  INV-4: UnityBounds.center == Center
         UnityBounds.size == Size
         must hold at all times
end note

note right of Feature
  <b>IDENTITY</b>

  INV-5: Id is assigned at construction
         and never changes (get-only)

  INV-6: Name is assigned at construction
         and never changes (get-only)

  INV-7: Index >= 0 whenever the feature
         belongs to a FeatureSetRenderer
end note

note bottom of Feature
  <b>STATE</b>

  INV-8:  If Visible == false
          then Selected must also == false
          (cannot select an invisible feature)

  INV-9:  If Temporary == true,
          feature is hidden on deselect
          and never persists to storage

  INV-10: FeatureSetParent is either null
          (unassigned) or a valid live
          FeatureSetRenderer instance
end note

note left of Feature
  <b>DATA</b>

  INV-11: RawData is never null
          (may be an empty array, never null)

  INV-12: Flag is never null
          (defaults to empty string "")

  INV-13: Metric and Comment are only
          meaningful when feature belongs
          to the New (user-defined) feature set
end note

@enduml
